## Project Overview

### What is DAL?

DAL (DeepSeek Automation Linux) is a command-line interface (CLI) tool that automates Linux tasks using the DeepSeek language model. This tool works with web automation (Playwright) and can:

- Automatically log into DeepSeek accounts
- Send user messages to the model
- Receive and analyze model responses
- Execute Linux commands in the terminal
- Return results to the model to determine the next step

### Project Goals

The main objectives of this project are to:
- Perform complex Linux tasks step by step
- Automatically check and install prerequisites
- Identify and resolve errors
- Simplify installation and configuration processes

### Technologies Used

| Technology | Version | Purpose |
|------------|---------|---------|
| Python | 3.10+ | Main programming language |
| Playwright | latest | Browser automation |
| playwright_stealth | latest | Prevent automation detection |
| Colorama | latest | Terminal output coloring |
| Termcolor | latest | Text coloring |

